Well, Cook, I guess you kinda knew that coming in, didn't you?  His house, his rules.  If the conversations become more of proving a point than resolving issues that arise between vet and non-vet, then there may be a need for moderation.  The initail point of this site was to promote an open dialog from both sides.  <br>
If the dialog got too abusive or too heated.  Both sides agreed to disagree.  There are many issues that both sides could come to agreement on.<br>
The focus for many of the threads center around nothing but Spatz. How get Spatz, how to discredit Spatz, how to intimidate Spatz, how to prove Spatz is wrong, a communist, a hippy, a anti-vet hater.  If anything was proved here, it was that Spatz was the main topic of discussion.<br>
The Brotherhood of Choice, the Warrior symbolism, the &quot;code&quot;, the &quot;pack&quot;, the &quot;Pack Mom&quot; all appear to be symptoms of issues not being discussed.  The issues about healing, PTSD, disablity, VA care, nite sweats, interrupted sleep patterns, intrusive thoughts are always being covered up by these other things.<br>
The sandbox is full, it may be too late to sift it clean.  Marc is not going to stand by and see it get any dirtier.<br>
Sorry, but that is my opinion.<br>
Chet Botkins<br>
1st. Cav 3/18th Arty<br>
RVN Oct.65-May 67
